### LEVEL CALIBRATION (R1-R6 Compliance Check)

| Rule | Implementation in This Email | Status |
|------|------------------------------|--------|
| **R1 — Symptom Over Label** | No level labels used. Descriptions: "verbal 4-year-old," "6-year-old with sensory differences," "non-verbal 9-year-old," "3 and just starting," "8 and you've been at this long enough." | ✅ |
| **R2 — 3-5 Recognition Anchors** | Three anchors in the Hook (pause, look down, pull at waistband / nothing visible). Three explicit testimonials covering L1, L2, L3 experiences. Parent quotes mention specific child types without level labels. | ✅ |
| **R3 — Age Ranges Instead of Fixed Ages** | "3 and just starting" / "8 and you've been at this" (Hook). Testimonials: "verbal 4-year-old," "6-year-old with sensory differences," "non-verbal 9-year-old." Offer and mechanism: "For kids 3 to 10+." No "toddler" or "preschooler." | ✅ |
| **R4 — Verbal/Non-Verbal Inclusivity** | Hook: "saying 'wet' or showing you with a gesture." Testimonials: verbal 4yo ("said 'wet'") AND non-verbal 9yo ("walks differently"). Mechanism: "verbal or non-verbal." Recognition anchors: "pause, look down, pull at the waistband, saying 'wet' or showing you." | ✅ |
| **R5 — Timeline Flexibility** | "Some kids take 2 weeks. Others take 8. Both are normal." No fixed promises. "30 more days of consistent wear" framed as possibility, not guarantee. Testimonials show Week 3, Week 4, 1 month — no uniform timeline. | ✅ |
| **R6 — Low-Bar Success Metrics** | Success metrics: "pause," "look down," "pull at waistband," "walking differently," "said 'wet' for the first time." Never: "fully trained," "accident-free," "just like other kids." P.S. reinforces: "works on its own timeline." | ✅ |
| **Forbidden Language** | No "easy / quick / simple." No "just like other kids." No comparison to neurotypical development. No "Level 1/2/3" labels. No "adult diapers" or "forever in pull-ups." No BCBA-specific jargon (L1 would not relate). No urgency manipulation for L3 (soft dual CTA). | ✅ |

